<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder"
             xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui"
             xmlns:b="urn:import:org.gwtbootstrap3.client.ui"
             xmlns:rdl="urn:import:com.therdl.client.view.widget"
        >

    <ui:with field="res" type="com.therdl.client.view.cssbundles.Resources"/>

    <ui:style>

	   .push {
	        padding-top: 60px;
	    }

        .socialPanel {
            padding-left: 150px;
        }

        .logoPanel {
            height: 300px;
            width: 390px;
        }

        .mainContainer {
            width: 390px;
            height: 320px;
            overflow: visible;
        }

        .titlePanel {
            width: 100%;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding-top: 30px;
        }

    </ui:style>


    <g:HTMLPanel>

        <rdl:AppMenu ui:field="appMenu"/>

            <b:Container addStyleNames="{style.push}">
                <b:Row>
                    <b:Column size="MD_4">
                        <g:AbsolutePanel styleName="{style.mainContainer}">
                            <b:Button ui:field="compatibilityCat" text="Compatibility"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="connectionCat" text="Connection"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="exteriorCat" text="Exterior"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="eroticismCat" text="Eroticism"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="seductionCat" text="Seduction"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="psyTendCat" text="Psy Tend"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="affairsCat" text="Affairs"/>
                            <b:Button ui:field="abuseCat" text="Abuse"/>

                            <g:at left='0' top='0'>
                                <g:AbsolutePanel styleName="{style.logoPanel}">
                                    <g:at left='90' top='10'>
                                        <g:Image ui:field="logo" resource='{res.landingImage}'/>
                                    </g:at>
                                </g:AbsolutePanel>
                            </g:at>

                            <g:at left='85' top='205'>
                                <b:Button ui:field="welcomeVideoButton">Load introduction video</b:Button>
                            </g:at>

                            <g:at left='70' top='280'>
                                <g:VerticalPanel>
                                    <rdl:SocialPanel ui:field="socialPanel"/>
                                </g:VerticalPanel>

                            </g:at>
                        </g:AbsolutePanel>
                    </b:Column>
                    <b:Column size="MD_8">
                        <g:HTMLPanel styleName="{style.titlePanel}">

                            <h1>The Relationship Driving License
                                <sup>PRE-ALPHA</sup>
                            </h1>

                            <h3 class="margin-base-vertical text-center">Things have changed.</h3>


                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    You don’t need an expert to tell you that in the past couple of generations in most
                                    cultures around the world, the context in which long term romantic erotic
                                    relationships
                                    evolve has changed.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    It seems to me that a relationship has to stand much more on it’s own two feet now
                                    else
                                    it fails. I think these changes are overall for the better because they have given
                                    rise
                                    to the need for people to think seriously about and develop solid relationship
                                    skills
                                    and habits.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    The stigma associated with break ups and divorce is much lower.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    Women are now more financially independent as they should be given equal rights to
                                    men
                                    and they choose just as men do to be career focused as well as family focused and
                                    the
                                    balance between the two is a challenge.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    Both partners expect high levels of attraction and eroticism as well as connection
                                    throughout their relationship as a given, while this is obvious to most readers it’s
                                    a
                                    fairly new idea in most cultures.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    Couples are now more atomic. Where in previous generations a couple would live with
                                    an
                                    extended community that would help with emotional, perhaps financial and child
                                    raising
                                    support partners now have to rely on each other for all these things.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    It seems to me that if we choose to build a solid healthy long term relationship we
                                    need
                                    to have a range of skills and habits and I look around and I see that generally
                                    speaking
                                    we do not have them. We therefore need to learn what they are and practice them.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    They way we should learn in my opinion is from each other. Indeed how else can we
                                    learn?
                                    Current relationship experts are just those who had access to the intimacy of many
                                    people. Each person has a story to tell, valuable information to share. Each one of
                                    you
                                    is an expert in your own relationship because it’s yours and you’ve learned precious
                                    lessons going through it. The problem is that buy and large we don’t share these
                                    lessons. They are locked away behind cultural taboos, especially the ones around
                                    eroticism.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    This is why The Relationship Driving license is being developed. Through the
                                    anonymity
                                    of the internet we set aside a lot of the barriers to free and deep discussion.
                                    &nbsp;Here
                                    you can come in completely anonymous, share your story and find advice and support
                                    as
                                    you will discover that whatever you are going through, you are not alone. Many
                                    others
                                    share in your joy or sorrow. Here you can take the lessons you learned and
                                    contribute
                                    them and rate and reference others contributions as we build a repository of solid
                                    relationship information and habits.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: justify;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    And what if we had a mechanism to filter and rate snips of information, to refine
                                    our
                                    understanding when necessary? After all relationships are very complex and there are
                                    many questions that I myself would like to get answers for.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <br/>
                            <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;"></span>
                            <p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: center;">
                                <span style="font-size:15px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">
                                    Well then I think we would have the foundation to the crazy ambitious goal to make
                                    romantic erotic relationships education part of the main stream. As we need history
                                    we
                                    need the skills and habits to build relationships.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <h3 class="margin-base-vertical text-center">Welcome to the Relationship Driving License!
                            </h3>

                        </g:HTMLPanel>
                    </b:Column>
                </b:Row>
            </b:Container>
    </g:HTMLPanel>


</ui:UiBinder>